  <name>Unit 3:​ How Do You Approach Integrating Technology?​</name>
  <summary>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@000000,1," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/how-icon.png" alt="A green circle with a lightbulb in the center" width="75" height="75" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_left"&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@000000,1," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Unit 3: How Do You Approach Integrating Technology?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@000000,1," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;In the previous unit, you learned about why technology is important for instruction and learning.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
